<section xml:id="section-system-geom-terminology">

<title>Terminology and notation</title>

<p><dl width="narrow">

	<li>
	<title>point-parallel form (of a line in <m>\R^n</m>)</title>
	<idx><h>point-parallel form</h><h>for a line</h></idx>
	<p>
	the vector equation <m>\uvec{x} = \uvec{x}_0 + t \uvec{p}</m>, where
	<m>\uvec{x}_0</m> is a vector from the origin to a known point on the line,
	<m>\uvec{p}</m> is a known parallel vector for the line,
	<m>\uvec{x}</m> is a variable vector representing an arbitrary point on the line (again as a vector from the origin), and
	<m>t</m> is a scalar parameter that varies as the arbitrary vector <m>\uvec{x}</m> varies</p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>point-parallel form (of a plane in <m>\R^n</m>)</title>
	<idx><h>point-parallel form</h><h>for a plane</h></idx>
	<p>
	the vector equation <m>\uvec{x} = \uvec{x}_0 + s \uvec{p}_1 + t \uvec{p}_2</m>, where
	<m>\uvec{x}_0</m> is a vector from the origin to a known point on the plane,
	<m>\uvec{p}_1,\uvec{p}_2</m> are known parallel vectors for the plane that are not parallel to each other,
	<m>\uvec{x}</m> is a variable vector representing an arbitrary point on the plane (again as a vector from the origin), and
	<m>s,t</m> are scalar parameters that vary as the arbitrary vector <m>\uvec{x}</m> varies</p>
	</li>

	<li>
	<title>point-normal form (of a plane in <m>\R^3</m>)</title>
	<idx><h>point-normal form</h><h>for a plane</h></idx>
	<p>
	the vector equation <m>\dotprod{\uvec{n}}{(\uvec{x} - \uvec{x}_0)} = 0</m>, where
	<m>\uvec{x}_0</m> is a vector from the origin to a known point on the plane,
	<m>\uvec{n}</m> is a known normal vector for the plane, and
	<m>\uvec{x}</m> is a variable vector representing an arbitrary point on the plane (again as a vector from the origin)</p>
	</li>

</dl></p>

</section>
